{"cursor":"3393","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'political party platform' or 'platform' is a list of the actions which a\npolitical party, individual candidate, or other organization supports to appeal\nto the general public for the purpose of having said peoples' candidates voted\ninto political office or complicated topics or issues. Individual topics, and a\nparty's, person's, or organization's opinion on them are often called the\n\"planks\" of their platform in reference to a basic stage made out of boards or\nplanks of wood, similar to what can be assembled for public speaking or debates\nto be held on.\n\nA party platform is sometimes referred to as a manifesto or a\npolitical platform.\n","linknr":165,"url":"Party_platform","recorded":1362578997,"links":27,"instances":["politics","theatre","united_states","politics","pamphlet","wood","politics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Political communication|Platform","Elections","Party programs"],"headings":["Origins","Famous political platforms","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6f/PamphletFrontPageProgressivePartyPlatform1912.jpg/150px-PamphletFrontPageProgressivePartyPlatform1912.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Society.svg/45px-Society.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["stage","theatre"],["plank","wood"],["common_sense","pamphlet"],["republican_party","united_states"],["progressive_party","united_states,_1912"],["mandate","politics"],["party_line","politics"],["stump_speech","politics"]],"members":["stump_speech","stage","republican_party","party_line","common_sense","progressive_party","plank","mandate"],"related":["Political_